Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 2cm slices, then chop into thin, 1cm-thick fries (no need to peel). Pop the fries onto a large, low-sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary - you want the fries nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(thinly sliced). Chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} as finely as you can (stalks and all). Pick the @tarragon{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks (discard the stalks) and finely chop. Peel the @garlic clove{1}, pop it into a small piece of #foil with a drizzle of @olive oil{for the salsa} and scrunch to enclose it.

About halfway through the fries' cooking time, pop the garlic parcel onto the fries baking tray and roast for the remaining time until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Add the tarragon and parsley to a #bowl, along with the @Dijon mustard{10%g}. Cut the @lemon{1} in half and squeeze in some juice. Season with salt and pepper and whisk together with a #fork. Keep aside for now.

Heat the @unsalted butter{10%g} in a medium #saucepan on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion, season with salt and pepper and fry gently until soft and sweet, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

When the onions have softened, stir in the @peas{120%g}. Allow to heat through, ~{1-2%minutes}, then take off the heat. Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed, then cover to keep warm.

About 5 mins before everything is ready, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{for frying} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. When the oil is hot, lay the steaks in the pan. Season with salt and pepper and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side.

Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want them medium-rare.

> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like them more cooked.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer to a #cutting board{}, cover with #foil and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

While the steak rests, warm up the peas (if needed). Open up the roasted garlic parcel and, keeping it on the foil, mash the garlic with the back of a #fork. Add it to the salsa verde, mixing it in well. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt or pepper if needed, then cut any remaining lemon into wedges.

Transfer the steaks to your plates and generously spoon over the salsa verde. Serve the rosemary fries, buttery sautéed peas and lemon wedges alongside. Enjoy.